In his speech at the APEC leaders' session, President Biden emphasized the urgent need for global cooperation in addressing climate change. He called climate change the only existential threat to humanity and stressed that every economy must take responsibility for finding solutions. The President highlighted the actions taken by the United States, including significant investments in clean energy and infrastructure, as well as efforts to increase international climate financing. He also emphasized the importance of preserving forests, reducing methane emissions, and mobilizing support for conservation efforts in the Amazon. President Biden urged all countries to take strong national actions and emphasized the opportunity to turn the current climate crisis into a moment of great possibility. The President concluded by expressing his eagerness to hear from other leaders about their climate needs and priorities.